      • isElementInDifferentModel

        public static boolean isElementInDifferentModel(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Package model,
                                                org.eclipse.uml2.uml.NamedElement namedElement)
        Simple check whether an element is in a different model than the passed package It will return true, whenever the the top elements do not match. This is always true, if the 2nd belongs to a different model, whether imported or not. This distinction is however not required in our context.

        public static org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Classifier> getReferencedClassifiers(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Classifier classifier)
